Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{2} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}, turning halfway.

Put the @British Hickory Smoked Sausages{2} on another baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{20-25%minutes}, turning halfway. IMPORTANT: The sausage is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. When hot, add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{60%g} and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden and turning crisp, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir the @onion marmalade{40%g} into the pan along with the @water{}, bubble for ~{30%seconds}, then transfer to a #bowl{} and set to one side. Keep the pan!

Return the (now empty) saucepan to high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. When hot, add the @British Beef Mince{120%g} and fry until browned, breaking it up with a #spoon{} as it cooks, ~{4-5%minutes}. Meanwhile, thinly slice the @green chilli{1} (add less if you don't like heat). When the beef is brown, stir in the @Worcester Sauce{7.5%ml} and half the chilli. Allow the Worcester sauce to evaporate, then pour in the @tomato Passata{1/2%cup}, water for the chilli (see ingredients for amount) and a pinch of @sugar{}. Bring to the boil, reduce the heat and simmer until thick, ~{8-10%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The beef is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, combine the @mayonnaise{1} and @red Wine Vinegar{12%ml} in a bowl along with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the @coleslaw Mix{120%g} and toss to coat.

Split open the @Brioche Hot Dog Buns{2} and grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%g}.

When the sausages and chilli are ready, remove the tray with the sausages from the oven and preheat the #grill{} to high (just move the potatoes down to the bottom shelf). Put the buns on the baking tray you cooked the sausages on and pop a sausage in each. Carefully spoon the chilli over the sausage, easing it inside the bun, then sprinkle over the cheese. Grill until golden and bubbly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Divide the fries and slaw between your plates, then serve the filled brioche buns alongside, finished with a spoonful of bacon jam and a few slices of remaining chilli. Enjoy - and don't be afraid to get messy!

> BBQ night never looked so good. These chilli 'n' cheese topped smoked sausage are the ultimate all-American recipe. A serious crowd-pleaser, these chilli dogs are a winning weeknight treat or the perfect thing to twist up your next weekend barbecue.